    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102588</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A drama club is building a wooden stage in the shape of a trapezoidal prism. The height of the stage is 2 feet. Some measurements of the stage are shown here.</p>

<p><img class="h-max-height--9-lines" src="/image_files/29442.png" /></p>

<p>What is the area of all the faces of the stage, excluding the bottom? Show your reasoning. If you get stuck, consider drawing a net of the prism.</p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>292 square feet. Sample reasoning: The trapezoidal face is 180 square feet since&#xA0;<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47528">\((12 \boldcdot 10) + 2 (\frac 12 \boldcdot 12 \boldcdot 5) = 120 + 60 =180\)</span>. The side faces are <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="47601">\(2(13 \boldcdot 2) + (10 \boldcdot 2) + (20 \boldcdot 2)\)</span> or 112 square feet.</p>
</div>
